# Week 2: Automation & Infrastructure Sprint - GitHub Issues

This document outlines the granular GitHub issues required to execute the "Week 2: Automation & Infrastructure Sprint".

## 🏗 Issue 1: Jenkins Controller Orchestration (Local Docker)

**User Story:**
As a DevOps Engineer, I want a containerized Jenkins environment so that I can manage CI/CD pipelines locally without polluting my host system while maintaining persistent state.

**Technical Tasks:**
- [ ] Create a `docker-compose.jenkins.yml` to orchestrate the Jenkins controller.
- [ ] Implement persistent volume mounting for `/var/jenkins_home` to ensure job data survives restarts.
- [ ] Configure `/var/run/docker.sock` passthrough to enable Jenkins to run Docker commands (Sidecar/Dind-lite pattern).
- [ ] Document the initial setup process (unlocking Jenkins, installing suggested plugins).

**Definition of Done:**
- Jenkins is accessible at `localhost:8080`.
- A test pipeline can execute `docker version` successfully.
- Jenkins configuration persists after `docker-compose down`.

